Now if he was on Blake‚Äôs team with long straight hair, they‚Äôd love him ü§∑üèΩ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è he could do no wrong no matter how he wore his hair. They hating on Spensa too üôÑ The Voice ü§¨

A staggering arrangement by any measure. Terrence is...different, though. And this is what seems to be prompting all manner of negative responses/posts. Beyond the hype and need to find "the next" someone, Terrence's artistry is up there with the greatest musical arrangers on the planet (David Foster, et al.). All four coaches know this. But it is not what certain viewers have come to expect from The Voice. Aside from the obvious, Terrence breaks the mold of the all-too-familiar pattern of moving around the stage to get-and-hold one's attention--lest boredom enter the mind and cause emotional outbursts. Lest one forgets what The Voice and all other programming (-pun intended) is all about in the end: marketing and money--besides the weekly entertainment value (or not) factor. Even if Terrence is "voted off" he will still have a fulfilled life--beyond measure.
